:: Potential Security Vulnerability {"position":"1600,675","size":"100,100"}
As you begin working on the API for the pharmaceutical company, you start reviewing how device data is handled.

While testing, you notice something unusual in the device logic.

A value used during device resets is hard coded instead of being unique for each device.

At first, it seems harmless. But after digging deeper, you realize this could affect how the device behaves after a reset.

In some cases, the device may continue running with incorrect or uncalibrated settings. This could lead to inaccurate readings — either false alarms or missed heart irregularities.

You bring this up with a senior engineer.

They hesitate before responding.

''Engineer:'' "Yeah... we knew about that. It was supposed to be temporary, but fixing it would’ve delayed release. Management decided to ship anyway."

They lower their voice.

''Engineer:'' "They also don’t want to touch it right now… especially with the pharmaceutical deal happening."

This is no longer just about data.

This could impact patient safety.

----
[[Bring it up to your manager->Whistleblowing Dilema]]
[[Talk more with the engineer->Whistleblowing Dilema]]
[[Ignore it and continue working->Whistleblowing Dilema]]
----
([[Continue->Whistleblowing Dilema]])


:: Reasons to Sell User's Health Data {"position":"1250,975","size":"100,100"}
"Why are we doing this, is the company in trouble?" you bluntly ask.

The CEO sighs, dropping the corporate persona.

''CEO'' "Startups are expensive. We've expanded too quickly and the venture capitalist money is running out. Our charity program is also bleeding us dry. The pharmaceutical company is also willing to make a charitable 'donation' that would fund another 10,000 low-income patients."

''Manager'' "If you're worried about the legality, don't be. We snuck a clause into the Terms & Conditions months ago that allows for third party data transfers. It's perfectly legal as long as we anonymize the data."

''CEO'' "Try to think about it as keeping our mission alive"
---------
